with us, we're a full-service financial firm. So we offer investing, banking, advice for those

00:06:44.839 --> 00:06:50.679
who are interested in those types of things, all kinds of financial products. And so the last six

00:06:50.679 --> 00:06:57.000
and a half years or so, I've been at Schwab. And one of the cool things about my role has been,

00:06:57.000 --> 00:07:01.880
since I've been here for six and a half years, I've probably had five or six different jobs.

00:07:02.279 --> 00:07:09.720
I actually started in the marketing analytics space and working on new clients that were new

00:07:09.720 --> 00:07:16.920
to the firm and also referrals, and moved naturally into what we call journey analytics,

00:07:16.920 --> 00:07:23.640
so how customers go from point A to point B. And that can be everything from a micro-journey of

00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:29.000
you're trying to move money from one account to another account, to how you get onboarded,

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:33.799
how we find you as a prospect and turn you into a client and manage the lifetime of your

00:07:33.799 --> 00:07:43.559
relationship. So I spent about a year on the data science team doing that. And after that,

00:07:43.559 --> 00:07:48.279
moved into more of a role focusing on prospect conversion. This was on the call center team

00:07:48.279 --> 00:07:53.799
specifically, so supporting call centers and trying to use natural language processing and large

00:07:53.799 --> 00:08:00.519
amounts of text to try to determine why customers were calling us, what were their needs, how we

00:08:00.519 --> 00:08:04.839
could help them, those types of things. And then most recently, this is probably the longest

00:08:05.880 --> 00:08:12.119
tenured role I've had at Schwab. I've been in more of the product analytics and risk space,

00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:18.920
